title: Nordpool prices in a table
content:
type: horizontal-stack
cards:
  - type: custom:flex-table-card
    title: SPOT Today
    entities:
      include:
        - sensor.nordpool
    columns:
      - name: ''
        data: raw_today
        modify: new Date(x.start).getHours()
        icon: mdi:clock
        suffix: '.00'
      - name: ''
        data: today
        align: right
        icon: mdi:currency-eur
        suffix: snt
  - type: custom:flex-table-card
    title: SPOT Tomorrow
    strict: true
    entities:
      include:
        - sensor.nordpool
    columns:
      - name: ''
        data: raw_tomorrow
        modify: new Date(x.start).getHours()
        icon: mdi:clock
        suffix: '.00'
      - name: ''
        data: tomorrow
        align: right
        icon: mdi:currency-eur
        suffix: snt

Minion Work Assignments - Python
content:
# Minion Work Assignments
# =======================
# Commander Lambda's minions are upset! They're given the worst jobs on the whole space station, and some of them are starting to complain that even those worst jobs are being allocated unfairly. If you can fix this problem, it'll prove your chops to Commander Lambda so you can get promoted!
#
# Minions' tasks are assigned by putting their ID numbers into a list, one time for each day they'll work that task. As shifts are planned well in advance, the lists for each task will contain up to 99 integers. When a minion is scheduled for the same task too many times, they'll complain about it until they're taken off the task completely. Some tasks are worse than others, so the number of scheduled assignments before a minion will refuse to do a task varies depending on the task. You figure you can speed things up by automating the removal of the minions who have been assigned a task too many times before they even get a chance to start complaining.
#
# Write a function called solution(data, n) that takes in a list of less than 100 integers and a number n, and returns that same list but with all of the numbers that occur more than n times removed entirely. The returned list should retain the same ordering as the original list - you don't want to mix up those carefully-planned shift rotations! For instance, if data was [5, 10, 15, 10, 7] and n was 1, solution(data, n) would return the list [5, 15, 7] because 10 occurs twice, and thus was removed from the list entirely.


# # 1st attempt (tests 5, 7, and 9 fail)
# from collections import defaultdict
#
#
# def solution(data, n):
#     count = defaultdict(int)
#
#     for num in data:
#         count[num] += 1
#
#     return [k for k, v in count.items() if v <= n]


# # ChatGpt (GPT 3.5) (tests 5, 7, and 9 fail)
# def solution(data, n):
#     # Create a dictionary to count the occurrences of each number in the list
#     count_dict = {}
#
#     # Count occurrences of each number in the list
#     for num in data:
#         if num in count_dict:
#             count_dict[num] += 1
#         else:
#             count_dict[num] = 1
#
#     # Use a list comprehension to filter out numbers that occur more than n times
#     filtered_data = [num for num in data if count_dict[num] <= n]
#
#     return filtered_data


# # 2nd attempt (tests 5, and 9 fail)
# from collections import OrderedDict
# 
# 
# def solution(data, n):
#     d = OrderedDict()
#     for i in data:
#         d[i] = d.get(i, 0) + 1
# 
#     return [k for k, v in d.items() if v <= n]


# 3rd attempt (all tests pass)
from collections import Counter


def solution(data, n):
    count = Counter(data)

    return [i for i in data if count[i] <= n]


assert solution([5, 10, 15, 10, 7], 1) == [5, 15, 7]
assert solution([1, 2, 3], 0) == []
assert solution([1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 3, 4, 5, 5], 1) == [1, 4]

diff --git a/scripts/install_addon b/scripts/install_addon

--- a/scripts/install_addon
+++ b/scripts/install_addon
@@ -42,31 +42,43 @@ if [ -f ${ADDON_INSTALL_DIR}/${PKG_ADDON_ID}-${ADDONVER}.zip ]; then
   fi
 fi
 
+cd ${ADDON_BUILD}/${PKG_ADDON_ID}
+
+# fix resources
+ADDON_ICON=$(xmlstarlet sel -t -v "//addon/extension/assets/icon"     addon.xml || :)
+ADDON_FANART=$(xmlstarlet sel -t -v "//addon/extension/assets/fanart" addon.xml || :)
+
+if [[ -n ${ADDON_ICON} ]] && [[ ${ADDON_ICON} != resources/* ]]; then
+  rm -f resources/icon.png
+  mv ${ADDON_ICON} resources
+  xmlstarlet ed -L -u "//addon/extension/assets/icon" -v "resources/${ADDON_ICON}" addon.xml
+fi
+
+if [[ -n ${ADDON_FANART} ]] && [[ ${ADDON_FANART} != resources/* ]]; then
+  rm -f resources/fanart.png
+  mv ${ADDON_FANART} resources
+  xmlstarlet ed -L -u "//addon/extension/assets/fanart" -v "resources/${ADDON_FANART}" addon.xml

+# remove distro fanart in case addon has it's own in .jpg format
+[ -f resources/fanart.jpg -a -f resources/fanart.png ] && rm resources/fanart.png

title: [v1] AHK Script for removing "Whats New" in Steam
content:
; Define class name and new properties
className := "libraryhome_UpdatesContainer_17uEB"
newProperties := "display:none;"

; Read the CSS file
cssFilePath := "E:\Games\Steam\steamui\css\chunk~2dcc5aaf7.css"
FileRead, cssContent, %cssFilePath%

; Get the original character count
originalLength := StrLen(cssContent)

; Find the class and replace its properties with newProperties
RegExPattern := "(\." className ".*?\{)(.*?)(\})"
cssContent := RegExReplace(cssContent, "s)" RegExPattern, "$1" newProperties " $3")

; Save the modified content back to the file
FileDelete, %cssFilePath%
FileAppend, %cssContent%, %cssFilePath%

; Count the characters again
newLength := StrLen(cssContent)

; Calculate the difference and add spaces to maintain the file size
charDiff := originalLength - newLength
spaces := ""
Loop, %charDiff%
{
    spaces .= " "
}
FileAppend, %spaces%, %cssFilePath%

class Base_net(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super(Base_net, self).__init__()
        
    def set_neurons(self,
                    n_input_neurons,
                     n_hiden_neurons_1,
                     n_hiden_neurons_2,
                     n_hiden_neurons_3,
                     n_hiden_neurons_4,
                     n_out_neurons):
        
         
        self.input_layer = nn.Linear(n_input_neurons, n_hiden_neurons_1)
        self.input_activation_func = nn.ReLU()

        self.hiden_layer_1 = nn.Linear(n_hiden_neurons_1, n_hiden_neurons_2)
        self.activation_func_1 = nn.ReLU()

        self.hiden_layer_2 = nn.Linear(n_hiden_neurons_2, n_hiden_neurons_3)
        self.activation_func_2 = nn.ReLU()
        
        self.hiden_layer_3 = nn.Linear(n_hiden_neurons_3, n_hiden_neurons_4)
        self.activation_func_3 = nn.ReLU()
        
        self.hiden_layer_4 = nn.Linear(n_hiden_neurons_4, n_out_neurons)
        
        
    def forward(self, x):
        out = self.input_layer(x)
        out = self.input_activation_func(out)

        out = self.hiden_layer_1(out)
        out = self.activation_func_1(out)

        out = self.hiden_layer_2(out)
        out = self.activation_func_2(out)
        
        out = self.hiden_layer_3(out)
        out = self.activation_func_3(out)
        
        out = self.hiden_layer_4(out)
        
        return out
    
    
    def set_learning(self, loss_function, optimazer, count_epoch):
        self.loss_function_ = loss_function
        self.optimazer_ = optimazer
        self.count_epoch_ = count_epoch

    def fit(self, X_train, Y_train):
        for i in range(self.count_epoch_):
            self.optimazer_.zero_grad()
            train_pred = self.forward(X_train)
            loss_value = self.loss_function_(train_pred, Y_train)
            loss_value.backward(retain_graph=True)
            self.optimazer_.step()
            if i % 100 == 0:
                print(loss_value)

    def predict(self, x):
        self.eval()
        return self.forward(x)


base_net = Base_net()
base_net.set_neurons(n_input_neurons = n_neurons,
                    n_hiden_neurons_1 = n_neurons,
                    n_hiden_neurons_2 = n_neurons,
                    n_hiden_neurons_3 = n_neurons,
                    n_hiden_neurons_4 = n_neurons,
                    n_out_neurons = 1)

nn.init.kaiming_normal_(base_net.input_layer.weight, mode='fan_in', nonlinearity='relu');
nn.init.kaiming_normal_(base_net.hiden_layer_1.weight, mode='fan_in', nonlinearity='relu');
nn.init.kaiming_normal_(base_net.hiden_layer_2.weight, mode='fan_in', nonlinearity='relu');
nn.init.kaiming_normal_(base_net.hiden_layer_3.weight, mode='fan_in', nonlinearity='relu');
nn.init.kaiming_normal_(base_net.hiden_layer_4.weight, mode='fan_in', nonlinearity='linear');

#иннициализируются парамметры для обучения, как оптимизатор, размер батса, уол-во батче и т.д
base_net.set_learning(torch.nn.MSELoss(),
                     torch.optim.Adam(base_net.parameters(), lr=1.0e-3),
                     count_epoch = 500,)



class Net(Base_net):
    def __init__(self):
        super(Net, self).__init__()
        self.best_params_ = {}
        self.best_search_rmse_ = float('inf')
        
        
    def set_neurons(self, n_input_neurons, n_hiden_neurons_1, n_hiden_neurons_2,
                     n_hiden_neurons_3, n_hiden_neurons_4, n_out_neurons):
        
        super(Net, self).set_neurons(n_input_neurons, n_hiden_neurons_1, n_hiden_neurons_2,
                     n_hiden_neurons_3, n_hiden_neurons_4, n_out_neurons)
        
        #иннициализация батч-нормализации
        
        self.hiden_1_bn = nn.BatchNorm1d(n_hiden_neurons_2)
        self.hiden_2_bn = nn.BatchNorm1d(n_hiden_neurons_3)
        self.hiden_3_bn = nn.BatchNorm1d(n_hiden_neurons_4)
        self.hiden_4_bn = nn.BatchNorm1d(n_out_neurons)
        
    
    def set_learning(self, loss_function, optimazer, count_epoch, butch_size, drop_out_size, count_butch):
        
        super(Net, self).set_learning(loss_function, optimazer, count_epoch)
        
        self.butch_size_ = butch_size
        self.drop_out_size_ = drop_out_size
        self.count_butch_ = count_butch
        
        #иннициализация drop out
        self.hiden_1_dp = nn.Dropout(drop_out_size['hiden_1'])
        self.hiden_2_dp = nn.Dropout(drop_out_size['hiden_2'])
        self.hiden_3_dp = nn.Dropout(drop_out_size['hiden_3'])
    
    def forward(self, x):
        out = self.input_layer(x)
        out = self.input_activation_func(torch.Tensor(out))
        
        out = self.hiden_1_dp(out)
        out = self.hiden_layer_1(out)
        out = self.hiden_1_bn(out)
        out = self.activation_func_1(torch.Tensor(out))
        
        out = self.hiden_2_dp(out)
        out = self.hiden_layer_2(out)
        out = self.hiden_2_bn(out)
        out = self.activation_func_2(torch.Tensor(out))
        
        out = self.hiden_3_dp(out)
        out = self.hiden_layer_3(out)
        out = self.hiden_3_bn(out)
        out = self.activation_func_3(torch.Tensor(out))
        
        out = self.hiden_layer_4(out)
        
        return out
    
    
    def fit(self, X_train, Y_train):
        for num_epoch in range(self.count_epoch_):
            indexes = np.random.permutation(len(X_train))
            start_idx = 0
            end_idx = 0

            for num_butch in range(self.count_butch_):
                start_idx = num_butch * self.butch_size_
                end_idx = start_idx + self.butch_size_
                butch_idx = indexes[start_idx:end_idx]
                butch_X_train = X_train[butch_idx]
                butch_Y_train = Y_train[butch_idx]

                self.optimazer_.zero_grad()
                train_pred = self.forward(butch_X_train)
                loss_value = self.loss_function_(train_pred, butch_Y_train)
                loss_value.backward(retain_graph=True)
                self.optimazer_.step()

            if num_epoch % 100 == 0:
                print('epoch:', num_epoch)
                print(loss_value)
                print('============================')
        
        self.optimazer_.zero_grad()
        
    def search_params(self, X_train, Y_test, params_dict):
        for butch_size in params_dict['butch_size']:
            for count_butch in params_dict['count_butch']:
                for i in range(len(params_dict['drop_out_size'])):
                    print('butch_size:', butch_size)
                    print('count_butch', count_butch)
                    print(params_dict['drop_out_size'][i])
                    
                    self.set_learning(torch.nn.MSELoss(), torch.optim.Adam(base_net.parameters(), lr=1.0e-3),
                                     butch_size = butch_size, count_butch = count_butch,
                                     drop_out_size = params_dict['drop_out_size'][i], count_epoch = 500)
                    
                    self.fit(X_train, Y_test)
                    train_predict = self.predict(X_train)
                    
                    train_predict = train_predict.detach().numpy().astype(np.float32)
                    train_predict = np.array([x[0] for x in train_predict])
                    print(train_predict)
                    
                    search_rmse = MSE(Y_train, train_predict)**(1/2)
                    print(search_rmse)
                    
                    if search_rmse < self.best_search_rmse_:
                        self.best_params_['butch_size'] = butch_size
                        self.best_params_['count_butch'] = count_butch
                        self.best_params_['drop_out_size'] = params_dict['drop_out_size'][i]
                        self.best_search_rmse_ = search_rmse


#иннициализируются парамметры для обучения, как оптимизатор, размер батса, уол-во батче и т.д
base_net.set_learning(torch.nn.MSELoss(),
                     torch.optim.Adam(base_net.parameters(), lr=1.0e-3),
                     count_epoch = 500,)
